{"id":"CJq1X5","title":"Fleece.Core v1.7.1 DependencyService LexoRank sort order incompatibility","titleLastUpdate":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00","titleModifiedBy":"Homespun Bot","description":"DependencyService.MoveUpAsync uses Fleece.Core LexoRank (alphabet: a-z) to compute midpoints, but the resulting sort orders don\u0027t sort correctly under ordinal string comparison. For example, GetMiddleRank(null, \u0027aaa\u0027) returns \u0027annn\u0027 which sorts AFTER \u0027aaa\u0027 in ordinal comparison. This prevents using DependencyService for MoveUp operations when the codebase relies on ordinal comparison for sort orders. MoveDown works correctly because midpoints after existing values sort correctly under ordinal. Blocked upgrading MoveSeriesSiblingAsync to use DependencyService.","descriptionLastUpdate":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00","descriptionModifiedBy":"Homespun Bot","status":"Open","statusLastUpdate":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00","statusModifiedBy":"Homespun Bot","type":"Bug","typeLastUpdate":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00","typeModifiedBy":"Homespun Bot","linkedIssues":[],"linkedIssuesLastUpdate":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00","linkedIssuesModifiedBy":"Homespun Bot","parentIssues":[],"tags":[],"tagsLastUpdate":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00","tagsModifiedBy":"Homespun Bot","executionMode":"Series","createdBy":"Homespun Bot","createdByLastUpdate":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00","lastUpdate":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00","createdAt":"2026-03-25T00:11:44.8635338+00:00"}
